NITK Surathkal and IIT Jodhpur Sign MoU for Research Collaboration 

NIT Karnataka, Surathkal, and IIT Jodhpur have signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) to collaborate on multiple fronts, including education, research and outreach. The MoU aims to encourage faculty members from both institutions to collaborate on joint research projects in mutually interesting domains and disciplines. 
The MoU includes offering direct admission to Ph.D. programmes at IIT Jodhpur for meritorious B.Tech. students from NITK. Students ranked among the top 10 in their class who have a CGPA of 8.0 or above will be eligible for direct admission to the Ph.D. programme without the need to appear for and qualify in GATE or any written examination. 

Speaking on the occasion, Prof. Avinash Kumar Agarwal, Director of IIT Jodhpur said that this will be the beginning of a long-term collaboration between the two institutes. He invited the faculty of NITK to visit IIT-J and discuss with their counterparts. He also shared his views about NEP 2020, and mentioned the need for a highly flexible curriculum. 

Prof. B. Ravi, Director of NITK, welcomed the collaboration. Deans and Heads of different departments, who were present to witness the MoU-signing, interacted with Prof. Avinash and queried him about the best practices at IIT-J. 

Prof. Avinash Agarwal would be gracing the 22nd Convocation of NITK on 23rd November 2024, as the Guest of Honour.

