üë´üë¨ RASHTRIYA EKTA DIWAS / NATIONAL UNITY DAY @NITK SURATHKAL üë´üë¨

NITK Surathkal successfully celebrated National Unity Day, also known as Rashtriya Ekta Diwas, on 30.10.2024 to honor the birth anniversary of Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel. This day commemorates the efforts of Sardar Patel, who played a pivotal role in unifying the country.

As part of the Unity Week, held from October 25th to October 31st, 2024, NITK organized a series of events aimed at promoting unity and solidarity among the campus community. These events included a Unity Run and a Unity Pledge. The Unity Run saw enthusiastic participation from over 400 individuals, including functionaries, staff, and students of NITK, who collectively showcased their commitment to the cause of national unity.

During the Unity Pledge, participants reaffirmed their dedication to upholding the unity, integrity, and security of the nation. They pledged to continue supporting the cause of national integration and to work towards fostering a spirit of harmonious coexistence and brotherhood. NITK Surathkal is proud to have been part of this nationwide initiative that promotes unity in diversity.

