NITK Surathkal's Innovation Research in 5G/B5G Technologies Earns C-DOT Fellowship C-DOT STAR fellowship‚ú®

NITK Surathkal's Innovation Research in 5G/B5G Technologies Earns C-DOT Fellowship C-DOT STAR fellowship.üëèüèº

National Institute of Technology Karnataka (NITK) Surathkal is proud to announce that Ms. Aathira G Menon, a research scholar from the Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering (ECE), has been awarded the prestigious Centre for Development of Telematics (C-DOT) fellowship through their STAR program.

This recognition, unveiled on World Telecommunication Day, acknowledges Aathira's outstanding research potential in the field of telecommunications. NITK Surathkal stands uniquely among top institutions, including IITs, as the only NIT to secure this award.

Under the guidance of her mentors, Dr. Prabhu K, Associate Professor, and Dr. Shyam Lal, Associate Professor, Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, NITK Surathkal, Aathira's research focuses on "Next-Gen V2V: Deep Learning-Driven Multipath Profiling and Vehicle Fingerprinting for Enhanced V2V Communication in Smart Cities." This innovative project aims to enhance vehicular applications for 5G and beyond 5G (B5G) technologies.

The C-DOT STAR program offers a fellowship of INR 6 Lakh per annum for up to four years, along with mentorship from research leaders and access to lab facilities. This support will enable Aathira to make significant contributions to the development of advanced communication systems for connected vehicles. We gratefully acknowledge C-DOT for this opportunity and recognizing young talent nationwide. Special thanks to Dr. Prabhu K, Dr. Shyam Lal, and Prof. Sharnappa Joladarashi for their invaluable guidance and support.

