#DrugFreeIndia Pledge at NIT Karnataka, Surathkal ‚òëÔ∏è

Today marked a significant stride towards a drug-free India as we observed the International Day Against Drug Abuse and Illicit Trafficking. This day serves as a stark reminder of the global imperative to address the challenges posed by drugs.

The theme for this year, "The evidence is clear: invest in prevention," highlights the significance of evidence-based approaches in combating drug abuse and trafficking. The ramifications of drug problems are far-reaching, affecting millions around the world, from those struggling with addiction to communities disrupted by drug trafficking and the resultant crime.

As directed by the Ministry of Education MyGovIndia In a show of solidarity, students, Deans, Administrative heads, Faculty, and Staff came together to pledge their commitment to this cause. We believe that investment in preventive measures yields significant benefits. Early intervention and community-driven initiatives are crucial in fostering healthier lifestyles.

We call upon everyone to take action: join the movement, share this message, raise awareness, and contribute to forging a future where individuals can prosper without the constraints of drug addiction.

