Glimpse of our Workshop "AWARENESS CREATION ON NEW CRIMINAL LAWS" at  NIT Karnataka, Surathkal 

In an era where laws are the bedrock of our society, understanding them becomes a necessity. The Ministry of Education has recognised this and mandated awareness campaigns at Higher Education Institutions (HEIs) regarding the three new criminal laws to be implemented on 1st July 2024 - Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, and the Bharatiya Sakshya Adhiniyam.

In line with this directive, a workshop was conducted on 25th March 2024 at NITK Surathkal. We were privileged to have Adv. (Ms.) Jayashree Rattihalli, a practicing lawyer, as our resource person. She guided the audience through the nuances of the new criminal laws, the modifications, and the implications of these modifications on stakeholders such as the common man, institutions, and the executive and judicial system.

The workshop was interactive, with participation from Deans, Registrar, ICC Chairperson and PIC women welfare cell, faculty, staff, and students. 

We believe that understanding the law is not just for lawyers but for everyone. Let's continue to educate, engage, and empower!

