Sharing the glimpse of today's DST-SERB sponsored workshop on "Safety Data Analytics, Applications in Mining and Other Core Industries (SDAAMCI) 2024" inauguration held at the National Institute of Technology Karnataka, Surathkal. The chief guest of the workshop was Prof. Uday Bhatt, Dean R&C, NITK, and the Guest of Honour was Professor Jhareswar Maiti from the Indian Institute of Technology (IIT) Kharagpur.

This week-long workshop, from March 6-12, 2024, is an opportunity for professionals across various disciplines to gain expertise in safety data analytics. The workshop will provide comprehensive training on the collection, analysis, and visualization of safety data, and the application of statistical and machine learning techniques to identify patterns, trends, and risks.

We are privileged to have Prof. Maiti, a distinguished educator with over 23 years of experience and a consistent listing in the top 2% researchers in the world by Stanford University ranking, as a resource for the workshop.

In addition, the workshop serves as a conduit for students and professionals to connect with industry leaders and colleagues, share thoughts, and acquire knowledge of industry standards.

In the current data-driven industrial landscape, the ability to analyze and interpret safety data is a vital skill. This workshop aims to equip participants with these skills, thereby opening up new career opportunities and contributing to the safety and efficiency of mining and other core industries.

We welcome 25 students from various states including Karnataka, Telangana, Andhra Pradesh to this workshop. We look forward to a week of learning and growth.

