üîåThe Future of Electric Vehicle Charging is Here: NITK Surathkal Showcases SUIT-EV: Smart Universal Infrastructure for Efficient Electric Vehicle Charging 

Electric vehicles (EVs) are the future of transportation, but they face many challenges and barriers in India. One of the most critical issues is the lack of a reliable and efficient charging infrastructure that can support the growing demand for EVs. That's why we at NITK Surathkal have developed a SUIT-EV: Smart Universal Infrastructure for Efficient Electric Charging. 

One of the highlights of our participation at #IIvenTiv2024 is SUIT-EV: Smart Universal Infrastructure for Efficient Electric Vehicle Charging developed by a team led by Dr. B. Dastagiri Reddy. This research introduces a groundbreaking solution for electric vehicle (EV) charging, offering both AC and DC charging capabilities, enhanced power quality, and V2X features. This innovative approach addresses key industry needs, such as dual grid charging, adaptability to existing EVs, and retrofitting capability. The #SUITEV has the potential to revolutionize the #EV charging infrastructure and promote a #sustainable, #clean-energy future.

We are proud to share that our team had the privilege of interacting with Hon'ble Minister for Education, Skill Development and Entrepreneurship, Shri Dharmendra Pradhan, at the #IInvenTiv2024. Dr B. Dastagiri explained the salient features and benefits of the #SUITEV to the minister, who appreciated the team's efforts and encouraged them to pursue further research and innovation.

Join us at #IInvenTiv2024, the biggest R&D fair at IIT Hyderabad where we are showcasing our amazing innovations. We will keep you posted on the latest happenings at #IInvenTiv2024. Stay connected and follow us on our social media for more updates. 

