Introducing VidhYug 2.2.1, the innovative e-scooter at NITK SurathkalüîåüíÅüèª

NITK Surathkal is at the forefront of a transformative shift in campus transportation by integrating Artificial Intelligence (AI) to optimise the usage of electric vehicles (EVs). This pioneering initiative is headed by Dr. Pruthviraj U, Project Head of the E-Mobility Team at the Centre for System Design (CSD), Professor In Charge Transdisciplinary R&D, and Prof. K V Gangadharan, Coordinator of CSD and Dean of Planning and Development at NITK Surathkal.

The E-Mobility project at CSD NITK is a remarkable display of dedication to sustainable transportation. The team has developed a diverse fleet of electric vehicles, including 15 E-cycles, 5 e-scooters, 2 e-bikes, an e-trike for organic waste collection, and a specially designed quad bike for the physically challenged‚Äîwith additional innovations in the pipeline. AI algorithms are employed to predict demand patterns and optimise the deployment and routing of these vehicles across the campus.

The system's predictive maintenance feature enhances vehicle reliability and extends the lifespan of the EV fleet, exemplified by the current e-scooter model, üîå‚ÄúVidhYug 2.2.1.‚Äùüîå This model, specifically designed for the hostel office at NITK and financially supported by the Mumbai chapter of the NITK Surathkal Alumni Association, represented by Shri. S R Bala, NITK Surathkal Alumni Association Global Secretary, symbolises user-friendly mobility solutions developed by the team.The innovative minds behind this vehicle include Poudhan Kumar, Dixith K, Manish E S, Vikas, Maclin, Niranjan, Prakash, and Shradha Shetty.

Today, at NITK SURATHKAL campus, the Director, Prof. B Ravi handed over the keys to the Chief Warden Prof. Pushparaj Shetty and team. The event was graced by the presence of Prof. Srikanth S Rao, the Dean of Alumni and Corporate Relations, Prof. K V Gangadharan, the Dean of Planning and Development, Hostel Wardens, faculty members, Hostel staff, and students. #makeinindia
