üéâWe are pleased to announce that Prof. Debashisha Jena, a distinguished faculty member, of our Department of Electrical and Electronics Engineering NITK, has been recognized as one of the top 2% scientists worldwide by Stanford University.üåê

üìäProf.Jena's work mainly focuses on  system identification and control using data-driven machine learning algorithms, and its application to renewable energy systems. Some of his works are based on analysing the uncertainties that arise from integration of different renewables such as wind and solar generation to large power networks.‚úÖ

üîåOne of his main areas of research interest is the probabilistic load flow (PLF) of large power networks in the presence of renewable generations. PLF helps to plan and expand the power networks, making them stronger against unexpected events. It also helps to optimize the operation of smart grids, which are an important part of our future energy systems.üìä

üôåüèªThis recognition is not an individual accomplishment but reflects the dedication and hard work of our entire faculty. Prof. Jena is one among seven faculty members from NITK who have been honored with this prestigious recognition. We will be sharing more about the other five esteemed faculty members in subsequent posts.üíÅ

ü§ùWe extend our heartfelt congratulations to Dr. Jena on this remarkable achievement.üíê

