National Institute of Technology Karnataka Surathkal has secured a grant of 6.2 crores from the National Technical Textile Mission, Ministry of Textiles, Government of India. üéâ

Dr. Sreevalsa Kolathayar, Department of Civil Engineering, will be coordinating the establishment of a state-of-the-art Geotechnical Textile Testing Laboratory as a national facility at NITK. The project aims to promote the use of geotextiles for various applications and train students and faculty in technical textiles.üëè

NITK has plans to introduce new courses on technical textiles and conduct advanced research on geotextiles. The center at NITK will host all basic equipment for element tests on soil and geotextile fabric, as well as advanced equipment for model testing on reinforced earth under dynamic loading and field tests.

Dr. Sreevalsa said they wish to make the facility accessible to all researchers in need, especially for the south Indian region, as per institute norms.

üëè Congratulations to NITK and Dr. Sreevalsa Kolathayar on this achievement! üëè

