Actor & Director Shri Prakash Belawadi, National awardee for best film in the English language in 2003, who was conferred ‚ÄúPratibha Bhushan‚Äù by the Govt of Karnataka in 2003 for his contribution to culture, recipient of Helpmann Award, Australia (2019) for Best Actor, Male in the play 'Counting and Cracking', was the Chief Guest for the Incident 2023 inaugural ceremony. Padma Shree Awardee & Environmentalist, Smt. Tulasi Gowda, Karnataka State Pollution Control Board Chairman, NITK alumnus Shri Shanth Thimaiah, was the event‚Äôs Guests of honor. Director (In-charge), Prof. G.C.Mohan Kumar, Dean Students Welfare, Prof. Narendranath. S, Registrar, Shri K Ravindranath, & team Incident felicitated the Chief guest & Guests of honor. 
Dean Student welfare, and Incident presented a cheque of worth 50,000 as a token of respect to Smt. Tulasi Gowda during the felicitation. 

During the inaugural ceremony, Shri Prakash Belwadi said "the future will be replaced by the AI/Technology, the biggest human desire would not be to erect compound walls, but to break the compound walls to be together. Technology is not the only solution to all problems; human values, Indian culture, and social institutions will serve as a guiding force in addressing key issues."

Shree Shantha Thimmaiah addressed the crowd, saying, "Saving the mother earth is each of our responsibility; young generation should support the effective implementation of government initiatives such as banning single-use plastic by adopting new methods/technologies to make the country free of environmental pollution."

Smt. Tulasi Gowda said: " Clean air and green environment is extremely vital for every living creature, thus, young generation should nurture the habit of planting samplings wherever feasible to preserve environment" 

