In view of #ConstitutionDay2022 National Institute of Technology Karnataka Surathkal organised a talk session on the tittle "Constitution of India" today @NITK Surathkal. 

Guest speaker was Dr. P. Anantha Krishna Bhat, Retd. Professor, Author and Philanthropist . 
Dr. Anantha Krishna Bhat enlightened the history of Indian Constitution,  briefed about the constituent assembly, and the rights given in the Indian Constitution. He also explained the importance of Fundamental Duties enshrined in the Indian Constitution.
He educated the listeners about  the articles of Indian Constitution and the procedures about reforms and recent amendments of the constitution. 

Prof. Prasad Krishna, Director (Additional Charge), Shri Ravindranath (Registrar), Prof. Mohan Kumar G C (Dean FW), Prof. Narendranath S (Dean SW), Prof Vijay Desai, (Dean AAIR), Prof. S M Kulkarni,(Dean R&D), Prof Nagendrappa H, (Liaison Officer), other Teaching and Non Teaching Staff along with Students participated in the talk. 

